data.content:
Yes! C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`. Both work without any special directives:

```csharp
Span<nint>  signed   = stackalloc nint[5];
Span<nuint> unsigned = stackalloc nuint[5];
```

On this 64-bit system, `nint`/`nuint` are 8 bytes each. The feature has been available since C# 9 (when `nint`/`nuint` were introduced) combined with the `stackalloc` in `Span<T>` support from C# 7.2.
